title: Shared compression is similar, but risks are different
body:
The language here might have been read to imply that the risks of shared
compression apply to Web Packaging.  This rewords that to (hopefully)
remove that implication.

@jyasskin does this make the text clearer?

title: Minor clarifications
body:
Some minor changes in the web archiving section:

* In one place `archival views` is changed to `archival replay` to more accurately reflect the terminology used in the web archiving community (although I have left the other occurrence of "views" in the next sentence as it is)
* Changed `pre-rendering` to quite the opposite `deferred representations` (and briefly explained it in brackets)
* Changed `attendees` to `the Internet Archive` in the `In one case related to attendees, a public figure disputed ...` phrase, because the matter was related to the Internet Archive and was used there for an example, not necessarily related to any of the attendees. I think using Internet Archive's name here is not an issue as the story is available on their official blog too.

/cc @phonedude
